This paper deals with the Virtual Network Embedding Problem (VNEP), which is a problem related to network infrastructure and resource allocation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also involves approximation algorithms and linear programming, which are topics related to computer science theory. Hence, cs.AL (Algorithms) is also a likely category. The paper also deals with optimization and resource allocation, which are topics related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are topics related to Graph Theory (cs.GT).
